column6: This is almost enough to make me care about basketball.
The post mortem starts here. A Basketball Jones for your viewing pleasure:
8 out of 15 times when a team went from a 2-0 lead to trailing 2-3 in a NBA best of seven series, that team still won the series.

They say a playoff series starts when a team loses on its home court. Let's call that the Basketball Jones check factor. Giannis is lost between the ears and Coach Bud is getting out coached. The only way to beat the wall/zone is to put Giannis down low or at the FT line and inside out the ball. I don't think they have that in the offense and there's no time to teach it. Kawhi has been superhuman and I expect that to continue. Teams don't die easy, so a good check factor with pretty good volatility. I'll take the Bucks at 5-1 or better. Maybe 9-2 on a good day. @Abin_Sur
